<MainLayout
  title="About Me"
  description="Who I am, how my work has evolved across market research, UX research, product analytics, and data science, and what kind of problems I enjoy working on."
>
  <section class="content-shell about-reading-shell">
    <article class="about-story">
      <h1 class="page-title about-story-title">Who I am</h1>

      <div class="about-story-prose">
        <p class="about-story-lead">
          I’m originally from China and have been living in the Netherlands for the past few years.
          I have an academic background in both <span class="about-highlight">psychology</span> and <span class="about-highlight">data science</span>, and over time my work
          has taken me across market research, user/product research, and analytics more broadly and deeply.
        </p>

        <p>
          I spent more than seven years working in <span class="about-highlight">international market research</span>, leading
          quantitative and mixed-methods projects to understand consumer behaviour and support
          business decisions. Later, I became more interested in how people behave in product
          contexts and how insights can be translated more directly into product decisions, which
          led me into <span class="about-highlight">UX research</span> and product analytics. That shift eventually led me to <span class="about-highlight">study data
          science</span>, as I wanted to build a stronger foundation in statistics and modern analytical
          methods. For me, these are not separate career chapters so much as one continuous path:
          <span class="about-highlight">understanding behaviour, asking better questions, and turning different kinds of data into
          clear, useful decisions.</span> My recent academic work in data science went very well, and it
          gave me the confidence to work much more deeply with technical tools and analytical
          workflows.
        </p>

        <p>
          I’m someone who enjoys both the <span class="about-highlight">people side</span> and the <span class="about-highlight">problem-solving side</span> of work. I’m
          naturally outgoing, talkative, and easy to collaborate with, and I’ve always valued
          building good relationships with colleagues and friends. At the same time, I’m <span class="about-highlight">highly
          organised</span>, <span class="about-highlight">strong in execution</span>, and usually the person who notices patterns,
          inconsistencies, or practical details that others miss. I like making things clearer, more
          structured, and more workable — whether that means shaping a research question, cleaning
          up a messy analysis process, or finding a way through a problem in everyday life.
        </p>

        <p>
          Outside work, I enjoy <span class="about-highlight">learning new things</span> and following whatever catches my curiosity. I
          like cooking, experimenting with coffee and tea, listening to podcasts, travelling, and
          exploring topics like consumer tech and AI tools. Lately, I’ve also been experimenting
          with <span class="about-highlight">AI-assisted coding</span> through small projects, including this website itself. I like the feeling of
          <span class="about-highlight">picking something up quickly, figuring out how it works, and making it useful.</span>
        </p>
      </div>
    </article>
  </section>
</MainLayout>
